{"title":"The best Apple TV deals","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/555374/apple-tv-deals.html","date":1732890278000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>Lots of people are probably hoping that Apple will discount Apple TV+, its steaming service, for Black Friday, like many of the streamers have done, often in conjunction with another service or hardware product. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://www.disneyplus.com/welcome/stream\">Disney+ is bundled with Hulu</a> with a saving of 85% (just $2.99 a month). <a href=\"https://www.peacocktv.com/plans/all-monthly\">Peacock has 75% off</a> its monthly plan ($1.99 month for six months). <a href=\"https://www.paramountplus.com\">Paramount</a> is $2.99 a month for a couple of months. <a href=\"https://www.britbox.com/us/\">Britbox</a> is over 50% off, so you can pay $8 a month.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But sadly Apple isn’t discounting Apple TV, however, there are ways to get free access to Apple TV+. As we explain in <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/673723/how-to-get-apple-tv-plus-free.html\">How to get Apple TV+ for free</a> you can get much more than the 7-days access Apple offers as a trial, or the 3-months you can get of Apple TV+ if you buy an Apple product. There are even some Black Friday deals: </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.roku.com/whats-on/subscriptions/offers/black-friday/d2c\" target=\"_blank\">Roku</a> is giving three months of Apple TV+ for free to those using Roku devices. (It is also giving away Apple Music). </li>\n\n\n\n<li>In the U.K. if you shop at <a href=\"https://www.currys.co.uk/brand/apple/apple-offers/apple-services.html\">Currys</a>, or on Currys.co.uk you can get four months Apple TV+ free this Black Friday. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Best Apple TV deals – Black Friday 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As for Apple’s set top box, the Apple TV, we don’t often see deals, but there are a couple below. 